text: Putnam County is a county in Missouri, United States. The county seat is Unionville. In 2020, 4,681 people lived there. The county was organized on February 28, 1845 and named for Israel Putnam, a hero in the French and Indian War and a general in the American Revolutionary War. ==References== Category:1845 establishments in Missouri Category:Missouri counties
title: Putnam County, Missouri
